1
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,540
=Fireworks=

2
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,860
=Episode 11=

3
00:00:15,439 --> 00:00:16,239
Wait.

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,879
What's it to you?

5
00:00:18,399 --> 00:00:20,399
With me around,
Qiao Wenjun won't touch Qiao Nian.

6
00:00:23,559 --> 00:00:24,800
Ready? Go.

7
00:00:41,399 --> 00:00:42,479
Alright.

8
00:00:42,799 --> 00:00:44,880
But there are too many of us.

9
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:46,359
It's better if we split up.

10
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:48,560
So what's our plan?

11
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,320
The people we sent are out of touch.

12
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,560
Those two fools probably failed.

13
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:56,679
Handle them properly.

14
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,000
Don't let them say anything.

15
00:00:58,039 --> 00:00:58,840
Understood.

16
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:05,519
How's the thing I asked you to do?

17
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,280
I've contacted the PR team.

18
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,359
They're pulling down
Miss Duan's negative news.

19
00:01:09,959 --> 00:01:11,319
I wasn't talking about that.

20
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:14,280
I meant, have you set up
the account to transfer the funds?

21
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,959
The offshore accounts are all set up.

22
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:16,760
Hmph.

23
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,959
She thinks fake evidence
will bring me down?

24
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,120
Tell everyone.

25
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:24,280
The factory's down for three days.

26
00:01:24,719 --> 00:01:27,840
Clear out everything in Warehouse 3.

27
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,599
Understood.

28
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:41,239
Here.

29
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:42,799
Thanks.

30
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,239
You again?

31
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:47,519
Thanks, my dear fiance.

32
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:50,200
Watch your words.

33
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:52,040
Okay, my dear fiance.

34
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,000
Call me Song Che.

35
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:57,200
Noted, my dear fiance.

36
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:03,040
Qiao Nian,

37
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:05,760
do I really have to work
with this woman?

38
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:06,840
Yes.

39
00:02:07,159 --> 00:02:09,120
Only Wen Li can do this.

40
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:14,520
I'll drive you mad. Now, drive.

41
00:02:25,479 --> 00:02:26,080
Come in.

42
00:02:26,759 --> 00:02:27,919
Ms. Qiao, this is bad.

43
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,759
What happened?

44
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:31,120
We found signs of someone
breaking into the security room.

45
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:33,240
Today's surveillance footage
has been destroyed.

46
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,319
Turns out, Qiao Nian's behind it.

47
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,520
But we found some older footage.

48
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,400
We saw Mr. Jiang in the factory.

49
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,759
He stayed in the warehouse
for quite a while.

50
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,360
I knew it. That's how Qiao Nian
got that fake evidence.

51
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:55,240
Jiang Zechen was helping her.

52
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:58,439
This must've been Jiang Xiao's idea

53
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:00,680
to drag me down with him.

54
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:09,240
Ms. Qiao, you're always so busy.

55
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,840
How did you find spare time to drop by?

56
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,879
Cut the sarcasm.

57
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,960
I knew your family

58
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,840
was behind the media backlash.

59
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,479
You're just good
at kicking someone when they're down.

60
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:27,719
Ms. Qiao, that's a bit harsh,
don't you think?

61
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,520
Let's get to the point.

62
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,599
Why are you here today?

63
00:03:33,599 --> 00:03:37,639
You had your son steal
the quality inspection report, right?

64
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,639
Ms. Qiao, why do you

65
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:43,159
keep blaming everything on me?

66
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:45,000
He's a man of his own now.

67
00:03:45,319 --> 00:03:48,439
I have no control
over what he chooses to do.

68
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:49,439
They don't even...

69
00:03:49,439 --> 00:03:51,879
Don't talk to me about this nonsense.

70
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:55,520
Jiang Xiao.

71
00:03:56,719 --> 00:03:58,360
We've got too much history.

72
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,520
If something happens to me
or this batch of goods,

73
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:04,000
you won't be able
to avoid the blame either.

74
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,719
I haven't even settled the score
with you yet for trying

75
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:11,360
to monopolize the market
with Song Group.

76
00:04:11,599 --> 00:04:13,000
Even if something happens,

77
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,360
you and Song Group
will have to deal with it.

78
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:16,680
What does it have to do with me?

79
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,720
I've said all I need to say.

80
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,560
I should be going now.

81
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,560
But Mr. Jiang,

82
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,839
think it over.

83
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:33,800
We're the real back-to-back allies here.

84
00:04:35,439 --> 00:04:36,240
Of course.

85
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:39,680
We've always been the best partners.

86
00:04:40,839 --> 00:04:42,399
Since we're the best partners,

87
00:04:42,759 --> 00:04:45,759
why don't you return
what your son stole?

88
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:49,800
Ms. Qiao, why are you in such a hurry?

89
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,399
Even if I want to get it,

90
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:54,639
I need to wait for my son to return.

91
00:05:00,079 --> 00:05:01,639
I know all about your business.

92
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,759
Even if I die,

93
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:04,040
I'll drag you down with me.

94
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:12,040
Like you can do anything.

95
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,000
Wenjun.

96
00:05:24,639 --> 00:05:27,600
Wenjun, why didn't you save me?

97
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:28,759
Stop bothering me.

98
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,160
Wenjun.

99
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:29,959
It's not me.

100
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:32,959
Wenjun, how could you be so heartless?

101
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,519
Stop bothering me!

102
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:38,120
You can't just abandon me.

103
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,000
Stop bothering me!

104
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,040
Go away!

105
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,839
Wenjun.

106
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,439
It really wasn't my fault.

107
00:05:44,439 --> 00:05:45,560
Wenjun.

108
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,519
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Dad.

109
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,680
I was wrong. It wasn't me. I'm sorry.

110
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,680
I'm really sorry.

111
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,519
Wenjun.

112
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:56,360
You can't be so heartless
and abandon me.

113
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,199
Forgive me.

114
00:05:57,199 --> 00:05:59,480
You can't just abandon me.

115
00:05:59,639 --> 00:06:02,959
You can't be so heartless, Wenjun.

116
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,040
(Ever since Dad was burned alive,)

117
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:07,879
(I've been haunted by nightmares
and fear every day.)

118
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,199
Let's just eat something here.

119
00:06:15,199 --> 00:06:16,759
Are you treating us?

120
00:06:16,759 --> 00:06:17,560
Yeah.

121
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:22,600
The food in this restaurant sucks.

122
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:27,319
Why not pick a better place?

123
00:06:27,759 --> 00:06:31,360
Well, you can just get up
and jump into the water now.

124
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:38,800
Didn't you say the food sucks?

125
00:06:39,439 --> 00:06:42,120
Well, I'm eating it anyway.
What can you do about it?

126
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,839
I'm eating this whole plate.

127
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,319
Excuse me, bring us 20 more skewers.

128
00:06:53,199 --> 00:06:54,079
What are you doing?

129
00:06:55,319 --> 00:06:57,680
I'm sending the inspection report
to the reporters.

130
00:06:58,279 --> 00:07:01,040
Now's not a good time, Ms. Qiao.

131
00:07:01,399 --> 00:07:02,160
Why?

132
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:03,680
Zechen already knew

133
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,560
that Qiao Wenjun
was going to cause trouble.

134
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:09,000
So he had me monitor
her IP address in advance.

135
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,759
She just sent out
a press release to the reporters.

136
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:23,319
She's trying to pin
the factory's forgery on me?

137
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,720
That's right.

138
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:28,439
But I've already
intercepted the information.

139
00:07:31,199 --> 00:07:32,480
We could also

140
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,199
send her the video
of her attacking people.

141
00:07:35,879 --> 00:07:37,839
Good idea. I'll send it now.

142
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:41,680
But this video will only
hold her back for a while.

143
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:45,279
Only if we get the product documents
with her signature

144
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,639
can we prove
that she's the one behind the forgery

145
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,480
and clear my name.

146
00:07:51,079 --> 00:07:52,759
Will purchase orders do?

147
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:54,000
What?

148
00:07:56,639 --> 00:07:59,079
Come on. I'm her client.

149
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:01,639
Asking her for the product orders
shouldn't be too hard.

150
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,120
Take this with you.

151
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:08,820
(Quality Inspection Report)

152
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,759
With Qiao Wenjun's personality,

153
00:08:10,879 --> 00:08:13,240
she won't just hand over
the documents to you easily.

154
00:08:13,839 --> 00:08:15,759
She'll find all sorts
of excuses to refuse.

155
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,040
But with this,

156
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,519
she won't be able to refuse.

157
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:19,879
Okay.

158
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,600
Alright.

159
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,839
Since it's settled now,

160
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,800
let's eat.

161
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:28,879
That's right.

162
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,199
When we eat,

163
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,319
don't talk about work.

164
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:34,799
Also, there's something
really important today.

165
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:36,159
What is it?

166
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:37,440
Excuse me!

167
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:47,440
This is...

168
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,879
We're celebrating your birthday.

169
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:51,679
Zechen texted me early this morning,

170
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:54,320
asking us
to celebrate your birthday together.

171
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,879
Thank you.

172
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:59,399
Alright, let's make a wish together.

173
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:13,559
♪Happy birthday to you♪

174
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:17,039
♪Happy birthday to you♪

175
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:20,919
♪Happy birthday to you♪

176
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:31,519
Thank you.

177
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,000
Qiao Nian,

178
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,240
what did you wish for?

179
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:37,000
Why are you so clueless?

180
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,700
If you say your wish,
it won't come true.

181
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:40,480
It's fine.

182
00:09:40,919 --> 00:09:42,279
I can tell you.

183
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:45,759
My birthday wish every year is the same.

184
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:49,360
I just hope to see my mom.

185
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,559
I didn't know your mom...

186
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:55,919
She ran away from home a few years ago.

187
00:09:56,810 --> 00:09:58,240
But I haven't been able to find her.

188
00:09:59,279 --> 00:10:02,080
Well, I hope you find her soon.

189
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,279
Same here.

190
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,879
Thanks for spending my birthday with me.

191
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,159
And thank you...

192
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,720
for always keeping me in mind.

193
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,200
(How did Qiao Nian know about this?)

194
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:39,330
♪So many words unsaid,
the deeper we fall, the more we fear♪

195
00:10:39,610 --> 00:10:47,210
♪Fate like a gamble,
locking us inside its game♪

196
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:51,050
♪Hearts at play, truth and lies,
who could ever know♪

197
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:54,850
♪Where this ends♪

198
00:10:54,850 --> 00:11:02,130
♪I try to walk away,
yet still step into the fire♪

199
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:06,460
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

200
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,580
♪Love turns into pain♪

201
00:11:09,650 --> 00:11:13,770
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

202
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:17,410
♪Yet I still want you close♪

203
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:21,580
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

204
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:24,890
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

205
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:29,460
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

206
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:35,770
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪

207
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:40,550
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

208
00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:43,770
♪Love turns into pain♪

209
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:48,210
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

210
00:11:48,210 --> 00:11:51,560
♪Yet I still want you close♪

211
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:55,790
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

212
00:11:55,830 --> 00:11:59,050
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

213
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:03,770
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

214
00:12:03,770 --> 00:12:10,850
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪
